		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				P.S. To set up stories for LDoN, I think it'll be fun to have a series of small components that will drop for people to collect and make their weapon, armor, and spells. <br>  <br> For example, the rogue, the warrior, the knight may allneed a hilt for their sword, thenn they can try to collect a different type of blade for each class, short blade for the rogue, broad blade for the warrior, long blade for the knight.  The spell components will help the casters to have something to look forward to. <br>  <br> Make these components relate to stories that can involve fighting some bosses in a LDoN dungeon, so that a single group of adventurers can have fun helping each other accomplish epics in minor steps of collecting items that can take many trips to these fascinating dungeons. <br>  <br> I would love to be hunting in a group one night when the rogue in my group is so happy his hilt dropped that his eyes gleam.  I will feel like I have just helped a rogue with his dream. <br>  <br> Make it so that we are helping each other win their own class specific items, and not compete in items as much. <br>  <br> I realize winning a roll can be fun at times, but the loot fights can be unpleasant.  It's one reason I no longer hunt in BoT.  I don't know what story there is in BoT aside from people twitching whenever a boss spawns and running there to farm.  The place just seems to be a lot of greed to me.  Then people cheat on NBG rules, etc.  Bicker bicker bicker.  Anyway, occasional shared pieces are fine, such as the hilt of a sword all melee classes can use. But over all I prefer to see class specific items which can make story telling more fun, because then the rogue will tell us what the piece that just dropped for him means to him.  It'll be one way to get the players to tell stories to each other.
