get it themselves they lived through those boards and stood in awe looking at furors armor. <br>  <br> Best thing SOE did? instanced zones. Now you cant bottle neck guilds, any guild at that level can complete the content. It takes out waiting list and raiding schedules. The majority of EQ is now high level players. Run through our noob zones and see how man noobs are there. Then run through POT and see how many LFG. or pov. or hoh. or pos bot pon etc etc etc etc etc. The game is evolved well past single group questing. And you know who did it? us. All of us, this is exactly what we asked for. <br>  <br> Point blank, EQ is filled to the brim with spoiled LAZY people who want to be spoon fed, who dont want to go to the spoiler sights and find quest, and think they have the right to all content, but wont raise a finger in effort to get there. <br>  <br> I found it amusing in that guys article he spoke of naggy raids and going to guk, but when people first went into guk there was &quot;guk raids&quot;. The first king raid I went on has 70 people. 70 PEOPLE in LGuk!! Naggy and Vox, lets slay the dragon! 70-100 people! nothing has changed in EQ, it just got more advanced. When you raid time how many can you take? 72. Look familiar? <br>  <br> the only thing I agree with is bring back BToB, GM events and holiday events (and support staff of course). The rest of EQ has evolved like it was supposed to, just like we wanted.
