		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Rexerox you've always had the attitude that casual players are &quot;lazy&quot; while in reality they are hard working people who don't have time to sitt for 8 hours in a stretch to raid.  LDoN only allowed them to break those 8 hours into 2 hour increments.  They put in just as much time &quot;grinding&quot; in LDoN as you do in &quot;grinding&quot; the yard trash in raids.  Raids are fun, but the reality is EQ is a business that is starting to find out the majority of the players who can not sit for 8 hours in a stretch may soon go to other games. <br>  <br> Many people in uber guilds are &quot;spoon fed&quot;.  They get the latest spell, item from gifts from their guildies.  They sit afk while the guild is raiding and gain flags.  I was in LDoN with some people from a Time guild on my server that could not find Upper Guk, and we had to guild them.  Hehehe.  We roll our eyes at them. <br>  <br> My bud who just joined the uber guild on my server has moved his FT from 13 up to 18, and int from 335 up to 412, and gained 1000 hp in 3 weeks of raiding.  He didn't have to do much different from what he used to do in LDoN with me.  Hehehe.  I just went to a raid the other day as a guest and it was amazing how easy it was.   So don't try to fool people into thinking raids are the most brillaint things you need to do. <br>  <br> I was told by 2 top Time guilds people that I was &quot;great&quot; when they saw me in LdoN, and &#8220;did an excellent job&#8221; in GoD trial.  People ask me why am I not in those uber guilds.  The answer is I can't log on during raid hours.  I only play at midnight.  I can work for many many hours to earn 1150 AP to buy an aug that will gain me 40 hp.  Do I even want to buy that aug?  No.  Right now I'm sitting on a pile of LDoN points just enjoying having fun with people.  I don't really care about uber loot.  What's the point of having 412 int when the cap is 355?  What's the point of 18 FT when the cap is 15?  I have fun in the game interacting with people. <br>  <br> Your attitude that casual players are &quot;lazy and dumb&quot; is a bit amusing. <br>  <br> I know you and I will never see eye to eye.  This article states it's time to stop catering to uber guilds, and many people agree with it.  I just saw this same article posted on other sites.  I'm not going to debate you much on this.  In the end what hapens to EQ is decided by market forces.  You can call people lazy all you like.  Just remember:  Unfortunately money is king.  The #1 guild on my server has many toons up for sale, and in fact, their MT has been sold 3 times so far.  Right now it's being played by a guy who bought it just to apply to the guild.  What skill does he have?  We don't know.  He's going to jump right into raiding and no doubt enjoy the raid context that most of us LDoN people can never see.  Did he &quot;work hard&quot;? <br>  <br> On the other hand: One of my friends who solo owned the MT for 4 months and you know what he did?  He sacrified the MT down to level 58 so he could use it to make his own 6-boxed LDoN group lower in level and do the normal level 60 LDoN to gain 200 AP an hour. He was making $1 million pp every few days selling points.  This will of course make you sick to the stomach with the sentiment that a &quot;soloing&quot; guy can do this.  Well, he worked very hard at it.  You try and 6 box and tell me if it isn't skill. <br>  <br> I tried to ask him to group with people.  He would not.  His chief purpose for playing in EQ was to meet challenges.  He was not here for grouping.  He prided himself in what he could accomplish alone.  But he sold all 6 of his accounts and left EQ when he saw GoD was too hard for him to handle. <br>  <br> I feel sad for him that all of his work--and he did work for months 6-boxing.  He owned Time equipment for his main character.  In the end he just quit.  but what's the difference between his quitting and the original top guild MT going EBay?  Not much.  They both got all the loot they wanted, then they were both bored. <br>  <br> Talking about this makes me laugh a lot, which is probably good for my health.  But I think you take this game very seriously, and you may get upset, so I will not argue with you.  Only to say: Good luck and sorry in the end it's rl money and Sony's bottom line that will decide the outcome.  In the past the casual player didn't really complain. Sony would lose uber guild players if it did not have leading edge content.  The future may not be that way anymore.  The days of uber guilds may soon be over.  This is why 4 top guilds left EQ, and it may not be a bad thing for Sony at all when you consider 98% of the players are not in uber guilds.  They don't have to listen to the &quot;whinings&quot; of uber guilds anymore.  Sorry to use the word &quot;whining&quot;.  But if you call casual players voice &quot;whiniing&quot;, the coin must have 2 sides to it. <br>  <br> You don't think you are here whining, but many out there probably think you do, friend.  You have been very helpful on this board on many occasios. I respect you.  And I really don&#8217;t have anything against uber guilds.  You guys want to have fun, too.  I get that radiing is a different kind of fun.  In fact, many do work hard in raiding guilds.  Many uber guilds do spend hours figuring out puzzles.  I love those kinds of players.  I have nothing against these people. <br>  <br> I have something against a game that does not offer me fun.  What's fun for me?  Grouping with people.  Lately it&#8217;s been hard to form groups.  Whereas it used to take me 15 min to put together a group, now it's quite often an hour or 2.  I sense Sony is losing many accounts and the revenue is starting to decline.  This is why Sony is trying to lock revenue with the recent offer of free expansions for one-year pre-paid subscription.  This is why Sony asked in a poll yesterday if we want EQ to handle trading of rl cash for characters and items.  It all has to do with Sony&#8217;s revenue.  There are signs in the winds, smells of stormy weather coming up for EQ.  I am just hoping to halp EQ live long and prosper.  I myself could not care less about uber loot.  Like I said again, what&#8217;s the point in 412 int and 18 FT? <br>  <br> My chief purpose in posting is make sure the majority of the people are having fun.  That's where the bread and butter is for Sony, and for the best of EQ.  Sadly, while the casual players used to put up with a lack of content, now it may be the other way around.  But we shall see.  Hopefully you will be happy.
