				Riktor you want sugestions? Ok <br>  <br> -I want to see all the lvl 20+ old world zones(old world, Kunark and some of Velious) redone. Mobs abit harder. Loot tables redone to reflect the current age of the game. <br> -I'd like to see the whole expansion of Shadows of Luclin redone. A good faction system between the 4 major cities and the smugglers(whatever they are called) some good quests associated with it and the VT key quest removed or made easier. <br> -After the zones are all redone I want to see the ZEM adjusted accordingly. Hard Far away zones give the good better exp. <br> -LDON, trash the point system and replace it with quests and rare drops from the dungeons. Add some non-timed adventures. Change the timer on the current timed adventures to not be this red message that flashes accross the screen. Add a medium difficulty level. Fix the actuall physical locations of the camps so they don't look like someone just threw them and whereever they landed they stay. <br> Add some more unique dungeons. <br>  <br> -Future expansions should be without flag or key requirements to enter any zone. If it is keyed then it shouldn't be that hard to get. Something more on the lines of the Seb key. There should be a good storyline and good faction system along with it. Quests associated with each faction along with others. <br>  <br>  <br> Summary: <br> 1. ZEM modifiers changed to really reflect risk vs reward. <br> 2. Loot table redone to bring them up to the times. <br> 3. Ultra Rare drops added to every mob <br> 4. Some older zones redone <br> 5. LDON redone <br> 6. Most of SoL redone <br> 7. Quests added to get people to tavel all over. But having the reward worth it. <br> 8. New content should have a good storyline,faction system and quests. Content for everyone that doesn't require a Key/Flag <br> 9. More spawnable raid encounters. <br> 10. Epics redone (oh I think they are doing this) <br>  <br> ...I can go on and on.  <br>  <br> oh...and yes I did stop playing <br>  <br>  <br> One more thing...I'll give and example. Sebilis. <br> Keyed to get into.(but fairly easy key) Large raid encounter deep within the zone. Exp and good drops throughout the zone. With ultra rare items that can drop off mobs throughout the zone.(ie. ODS and RBG) If more of the new content released after SoV where more like sebilis I think they would have keeped alot more people happy and playing.
