				- <span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Edited:</span> 6/6 11:45am (1 edits total) 
				<span style="font-weight: bold;">Edited By:</span> 
				<a href="/user.asp?usr=559276" class="AuthorLink">Riktor_before_IGN</a>			
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Totally unrelated note: If nothing else the constant spam of this Riddick movie's ad here will insure I do not see that movie. <br>  <br> -I want to see all the lvl 20+ old world zones(old world, Kunark and some of Velious) redone. Mobs abit harder. Loot tables redone to reflect the current age of the game.  <br>  <br> Why? what point would that serve other then to make actual new player's lives more difficult as high level players came to camp the new loot or have a harder time killing these new tougher low level mobs with their newbie quest gear?  <br> People level out of the 20's within days now as is, I agree they could add new content to aid people this level, like upgrades to the &quot;newbie&quot; armor quests, quest to restock supplies like bandages, food, more bags. Instead of throwing out the old loot I would have it be consumed as turn ins for these new quests. Or maybe minor quests that would add maps to their EQ folder as many do not realize where and how to download them. If you are talking about temporary events to make the low level areas more interesting like the dark elf invasion of west commons, sure, all for it. <br>  <br> -I'd like to see the whole expansion of Shadows of Luclin redone. A good faction system between the 4 major cities and the smugglers(whatever they are called) some good quests associated with it and the VT key quest removed or made easier.  <br>  <br> Luclin suffered from the fact they tried to do so many new things in that expansion and didn't really do any of them well or to completion. Standard for the computer gaming world- a bloated, rushed, buggy product, there is interesting content here however but again, unless you are talking about something similiar to the giant-dwarf-dragon competing factions in velious not sure what point this would serve after all this time. <br>  <br> -After the zones are all redone I want to see the ZEM adjusted accordingly. Hard Far away zones give the good better exp.  <br>  <br> They are somewhat implementing this now with the &quot;hot zone&quot; feature but I agree a good many of the ZEM make little sense. <br>  <br> -LDON, trash the point system and replace it with quests and rare drops from the dungeons. Add some non-timed adventures. Change the timer on the current timed adventures to not be this red message that flashes accross the screen. Add a medium difficulty level. Fix the actuall physical locations of the camps so they don't look like someone just threw them and whereever they landed they stay.  <br> Add some more unique dungeons.  <br>  <br> Add quests sure, more dungeons, sounds good. I agree an untimed adventure option (I suggested an &quot;explore&quot; type several times) would be fine for those most casual players so long as the untimed adv gave no points as a reward. The rest just sounds like nit-picking or that you actually think LDON is too hard for the average player. I could agree they should rebalance the rate at which points are awarded for successful advs, basically from level 20 to 50 you go from earning a meager 1 pt to about 15pts per normal adv. Then suddenly jump to 50 pts per normal adv by 65 this could definately use some smoothing out.  <br>  <br> -Future expansions should be without flag or key requirements to enter any zone. If it is keyed then it shouldn't be that hard to get. Something more on the lines of the Seb key. There should be a good storyline and good faction system along with it. Quests associated with each faction along with others.  <br>  <br> I agree if a flag or key system is purely there to force players to spend time camping drops to earn the privilege of camping the next zone it's needless aggrevation (see: the entire Luclin expansion). The idea that a zone that requires a raid force to succeed in would require each individual player to aquire 1 or more items that MIGHT drop ONCE every 20-30 minutes (at BEST!) and you would therefor need 30+ of these individual drops doesn't inspire anyone but those with way too much time on their hands to proceed. <br>  <br> On the other hand certain very high level encounters should require some steps. Like if you want to challenge that god in his home plane it makes sense to me you have to aquire item/key/flag X to enter, the difference I would make was that only 1 person per group would need to aquire this entrance fee, that way people who came later or missed the initial event are not locked out of participating with their friends and multiple people working together could aquire this key or flag for all group members at completion.  <br> Secondly, I would make the aquiring of that entrance fee a tangible reward in it's own right, so that there is an incentive for others to continue to complete or help others complete the task or quest, this could be faction that leads to other quests, or an item, or AA, etc.		

			</td>
		</tr>
