			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				&quot;Why? what point would that serve other then to make actual new player's lives more difficult as high level players came to camp the new loot or have a harder time killing these new tougher low level mobs with their newbie quest gear?&quot; <br>  <br> I didn't mean make them super harder. For example Castle Mistmore. Newbies now have it alot better. They can get a weapon in the bazaar for 100pp that was god-like back in the day. Revamp, add some HP/AC to these mobs slightly and add some drops that might actually be usefull for a level 30, 35 or 40 level player for awhile. When its new for the first 2-3 weeks yes every level 65 player will be slaughtering the zone but that won't last. You may actually see players going to these zones again. Maybe not. <br>  <br> &quot;unless you are talking about something similiar to the giant-dwarf-dragon competing factions in velious not sure what point this would serve after all this time.&quot; <br>  <br> Thats exactly what I meant...and unfortunatly after all this time no I don't see the point really. <br>  <br>  <br> &quot;They are somewhat implementing this now with the &quot;hot zone&quot; feature but I agree a good many of the ZEM make little sense&quot; <br>  <br> Yes I guess its a start. But they need to take it away from other places and the fact that they refer to it as &quot;Hot Zones&quot; makes me want to vomit. One more example of why the &quot;R&quot; in MMORPG does not apply anymore to EQ. <br>  <br> &quot;that you actually think LDON is too hard for the average player.&quot; <br>  <br> Nit-picking I guess and no the &quot;Normal&quot; adventures I think are too easy. &quot;Hard&quot; ones are about on the money. They are Hard for most. The point system I just see as a arcade style gimic. The game is ever&quot;quest&quot; and in reality there is no reason anyone under say...level 60 should waste time on adventures. Very little reward from them. <br>  <br>  <br> &quot;I would make the aquiring of that entrance fee a tangible reward in it's own right, so that there is an incentive for others to continue to complete or help others complete the task or quest, this could be faction that leads to other quests, or an item, or AA, etc.&quot;  <br>  <br> This is an excellent idea.  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> 
