		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				lol Sorry Siabra, Im not saying that the &quot;casual&quot; gamer is in any way lazy. Techincally Im a &quot;casual&quot; gamer. My beef is with people who rarely play the game but feel that just because they pay the monthly fee to play the game (of which.. they still get to play the game) they should be able to walk into any zone, have free reign of all the loot and get the best of the best. <br>  <br> Where as I think and agree with the devs that you should have to work, at least to a certain extent, to gain it. Dont you agree? <br>  <br> Its the two ends of the spectrum and the two extremes. One side says to make the game easier (which SOE has done, example AAs, level increase, exp bonus, exp nerf etc), the other side is screaming for high end content (inc VT, POP, GoD) and not to trivialize the game (to late!) <br>  <br> So Im sorry for the misunderstanding. The casual player makes up the base for EQ, but the normal casual player also knows there are zones that he/she will probably never see and accepts that. <br>  <br> As for me? Im a &quot;casual&quot; player too. Im in a raid guild, but I only log in anymore to hang out with friends, which is really what this game is about.
